- [Coding for Visual Learners: Learning JavaScript from Scratch](https://www.lynda.com/JavaScript-tutorials/Coding-Visual-Learners-Learning-JavaScript-from-Scratch/782143-2.html)

- it's more an ideal framerate.
- `framerate(rate)` (default is 60)
- `noLoop()` (on setup)
- **frameRate** is the number of times the draw function is executed in a second. If the **frameRate** for a program were to be 60, the **frameCount** after three seconds would be 180 (60 x 3).
- `text(value, x, y)`

